<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>PaloAlto Optimization Report</title>
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #1a1a2e;
      background: #f5f6fa;
    }

    header {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 60%, #0f3460 100%);
      color: #fff;
      padding: 2rem 2.5rem;
    }
    header h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
    header p  { margin-top: 0.35rem; opacity: 0.75; font-size: 0.9rem; }

    main { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }

    section { background: #fff; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
              box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); }
    section h2 {
      font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0f3460;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #e8eaf6; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    /* KV grid */
    .kv-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 0.75rem; }
    .kv-card {
      background: #f0f4ff; border-radius: 6px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      border-left: 4px solid #0f3460;
    }
    .kv-card .label { font-size: 0.75rem; color: #666; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
    .kv-card .value { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #1a1a2e; margin-top: 0.15rem; }

    /* Tables */
    .two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
    @media (max-width: 680px) { .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.88rem; }
    th { background: #e8eaf6; color: #0f3460; text-align: left; padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem;
         font-weight: 600; }
    td { padding: 0.45rem 0.8rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; }
    tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #fafbff; }
    .badge {
      display: inline-block; font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700;
      border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    .badge-agent    { background: #d0e8ff; color: #004a99; }
    .badge-baseline { background: #ffe0d0; color: #993300; }
    .badge-accept   { background: #d4edda; color: #155724; }
    .badge-modify   { background: #fff3cd; color: #856404; }
    .badge-inject   { background: #cce5ff; color: #004085; }
    .badge-prune    { background: #f8d7da; color: #721c24; }
    .badge-stop     { background: #d6d8db; color: #383d41; }

    /* Plots */
    .plot-wrap { text-align: center; }
    .plot-wrap img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 6px;
                     box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }

    /* Collapsible */
    details summary {
      cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; color: #0f3460;
      padding: 0.4rem 0; user-select: none;
    }
    details summary:hover { color: #e94560; }
    details[open] summary { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

    /* Caveats */
    .caveat-list { list-style: none; }
    .caveat-list li {
      padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem 0.6rem 2.2rem; position: relative;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0;
    }
    .caveat-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .caveat-list li::before {
      content: "⚠";
      position: absolute; left: 0.5rem; color: #e07b39;
    }

    /* Agent log */
    .log-entry {
      border-left: 4px solid #ccc; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; background: #fafbff;
    }
    .log-entry.modify { border-color: #f0ad4e; }
    .log-entry.inject { border-color: #5bc0de; }
    .log-entry.prune  { border-color: #d9534f; }
    .log-entry.stop   { border-color: #777; }
    .log-entry.accept { border-color: #5cb85c; }
    .log-meta { font-size: 0.78rem; color: #888; margin-top: 0.25rem; }

    footer {
      text-align: center; color: #999; font-size: 0.8rem;
      padding: 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>PaloAlto &mdash; Optimization Report</h1>
  <p>Pareto-guided Automatic Layout Optimization for Aligning Latent Topology in Omics embeddings</p>
</header>

<main>

  <!-- 1. Overview -->
  <section id="overview">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <div class="kv-grid">
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">Method</div>
        <div class="value">{{ method | upper }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">BO Mode</div>
        <div class="value">{{ bo_mode | capitalize }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">Cells</div>
        <div class="value">{{ dataset_summary.n_cells | int | string }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">Batches</div>
        <div class="value">{{ dataset_summary.n_batches }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">Cell Types</div>
        <div class="value">{{ dataset_summary.n_types }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">Agent Trials</div>
        <div class="value">{{ agent_history | length }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">Baseline Trials</div>
        <div class="value">{{ baseline_history | length }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv-card">
        <div class="label">Wall Time</div>
        <div class="value">{{ "%.1f" | format(wall_time_seconds) }}s</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. Convergence -->
  <section id="convergence">
    <h2>Convergence</h2>
    <div class="plot-wrap">
      {{ convergence_plot }}
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem; color:#555; font-size:0.85rem;">
      Plot shows best-so-far cumulative score (scIB + scGraph) over trials.
      Green markers indicate agent interventions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. Best Parameters -->
  <section id="best-params">
    <h2>Best Parameters</h2>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem; margin-bottom:0.6rem;">
          <span class="badge badge-agent">Agent-guided</span>
        </h3>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {% for k, v in best_agent.params.items() %}
            <tr>
              <td>{{ k }}</td>
              <td>
                {% if v is float or v is number %}
                  {{ "%.4g" | format(v) }}
                {% else %}
                  {{ v }}
                {% endif %}
              </td>
            </tr>
            {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <table style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Score</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {% for k, v in best_agent.scores.items() %}
            <tr>
              <td>{{ k }}</td>
              <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(v) }}</td>
            </tr>
            {% endfor %}
            <tr style="font-weight:600;">
              <td>objective</td>
              <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(best_agent.objective) }}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem; margin-bottom:0.6rem;">
          <span class="badge badge-baseline">Baseline (BoTorch)</span>
        </h3>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {% for k, v in best_baseline.params.items() %}
            <tr>
              <td>{{ k }}</td>
              <td>
                {% if v is float or v is number %}
                  {{ "%.4g" | format(v) }}
                {% else %}
                  {{ v }}
                {% endif %}
              </td>
            </tr>
            {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <table style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Score</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {% for k, v in best_baseline.scores.items() %}
            <tr>
              <td>{{ k }}</td>
              <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(v) }}</td>
            </tr>
            {% endfor %}
            <tr style="font-weight:600;">
              <td>objective</td>
              <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(best_baseline.objective) }}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. Best Embedding Visualization -->
  <section id="embedding-viz">
    <h2>Best Embedding Visualization</h2>
    <div class="plot-wrap">
      {{ embedding_plot }}
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem; color:#555; font-size:0.85rem;">
      Top row: best embedding found by the agent-guided run (cell type and batch coloring).
      Bottom row: best embedding from the baseline run.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. Metric Breakdown -->
  <section id="metric-breakdown">
    <h2>Metric Breakdown</h2>
    <details>
      <summary>Agent-guided — all {{ agent_history | length }} trials</summary>
      {% if agent_history %}
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>#</th>
            {% for k in agent_history[0].params.keys() %}<th>{{ k }}</th>{% endfor %}
            {% for k in agent_history[0].scores.keys() %}<th>{{ k }}</th>{% endfor %}
            <th>objective</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for trial in agent_history %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
            {% for v in trial.params.values() %}
            <td>
              {% if v is float or v is number %}{{ "%.4g" | format(v) }}{% else %}{{ v }}{% endif %}
            </td>
            {% endfor %}
            {% for v in trial.scores.values() %}
            <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(v) }}</td>
            {% endfor %}
            <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(trial.objective) }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
      {% else %}
      <p style="color:#888;">No trials recorded.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </details>

    <details style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <summary>Baseline — all {{ baseline_history | length }} trials</summary>
      {% if baseline_history %}
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>#</th>
            {% for k in baseline_history[0].params.keys() %}<th>{{ k }}</th>{% endfor %}
            {% for k in baseline_history[0].scores.keys() %}<th>{{ k }}</th>{% endfor %}
            <th>objective</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for trial in baseline_history %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
            {% for v in trial.params.values() %}
            <td>
              {% if v is float or v is number %}{{ "%.4g" | format(v) }}{% else %}{{ v }}{% endif %}
            </td>
            {% endfor %}
            {% for v in trial.scores.values() %}
            <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(v) }}</td>
            {% endfor %}
            <td>{{ "%.4f" | format(trial.objective) }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
      {% else %}
      <p style="color:#888;">No trials recorded.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </details>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Agent Log -->
  <section id="agent-log">
    <h2>Agent Log</h2>
    {% if agent_log %}
      {% for entry in agent_log %}
      <div class="log-entry {{ entry.action }}">
        <div>
          <strong>Trial {{ entry.trial_number }}</strong>
          &nbsp;
          <span class="badge badge-{{ entry.action }}">{{ entry.action }}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="log-meta">{{ entry.reasoning }}</div>
        {% if entry.params is defined and entry.params %}
        <div class="log-meta" style="margin-top:0.3rem;">
          Params: {{ entry.params }}
        </div>
        {% endif %}
        {% if entry.new_bounds is defined and entry.new_bounds %}
        <div class="log-meta" style="margin-top:0.3rem;">
          New bounds: {{ entry.new_bounds }}
        </div>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    {% else %}
      <p style="color:#888;">No agent interventions recorded.</p>
    {% endif %}
  </section>

  <!-- 7. Caveats -->
  <section id="caveats">
    <h2>Caveats</h2>
    <ul class="caveat-list">
      <li>
        <strong>2D projection quality is distinct from representation quality.</strong>
        High metric scores in 2D do not imply that the underlying embedding (e.g. latent space)
        captures biology well. Always evaluate the original high-dimensional representations
        independently.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Metrics are approximations.</strong>
        scIB-style and scGraph-style metrics are heuristics.
        They may favor certain dataset structures and penalize others in ways that do not
        reflect ground truth biological relationships.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Parameter sensitivity can be dataset-specific.</strong>
        Optimal <code>n_neighbors</code> and <code>min_dist</code> values transfer poorly
        across datasets. Re-optimize on each new dataset.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Stochasticity.</strong>
        UMAP and t-SNE are stochastic algorithms. Results may vary between runs even with
        the same hyperparameters unless a random seed is fixed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Batch correction and visualization are separate concerns.</strong>
        Optimizing the 2D layout does not perform batch correction. If batches remain
        entangled in the source embedding, no visualization tuning can resolve that.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Overfitting to metrics.</strong>
        Bayesian optimization can overfit to the chosen metric landscape.
        The recommended settings should be treated as a starting point, not a ground truth.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</main>

<footer>
  Generated by PaloAlto v0.1.0 &bull; {{ method | upper }} &bull; {{ agent_history | length }} trials
</footer>

</body>
</html>
